In a rare series of interlinked operations, 12 patients will participate in a 'kidney swap' at a San Francisco hospital.

The procedures - which take around three hours - will be performed Thursday and Friday at California Pacific Medical Center, with six organ donors and six recipients.

People in the chain are not compatible with relatives or friends to whom they are willing to give kidneys. So, they donate to strangers they do match. 

